Emacs I recently switched from vim to Emacs! Some observations commense here
Emacs is not a text editor! Well. not just a text editor&hellip; From the website: &ldquo;At its core is an interpreter for Emacs Lisp, a dialect of the Lisp programming language with extensions to support text editing.&rdquo;
What does this mean? Emacs is purely a lisp interpreter, same as you might find a python intepreter installed on your system.
